<title>USA: FirstFederal sets five-for-four split.</title>
<headline>FirstFederal sets five-for-four split.</headline>
<dateline>WOOSTER, Ohio 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>FirstFederal Financial Services Corp said Tuesday its board approved a five-for-four stock split and a 14.6 percent increase in the common stock cash dividend.</p>
<p>Shareholders will receive one new share for each four shares owned, effective May 22, and they will receive cash-in-lieu of fractional shares, the company said.  </p>
<p>The company also set a quarterly cash dividend of $0.11 per common share, payable May 22 to holders of record May 2.</p>
<p>The company said the cash dividend will be paid on the post stock dividend shares, representing an effective 14.6 percent increase in the cash dividend paid to common stockholders.</p>
<p>These actions reflect the confidence the board has in the company's diversification efforts and strategic direction,&quot; the company said in a release.</p>
